The paper deals with the analysis of linear independence of tensors, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). It also involves the study of assemblies of neurons, which falls under the category of neural engineering (cs.NE) and computational neuroscience (cs.SI). Finally, the paper uses techniques from discrete mathematics (cs.DS) to analyze the perturbation models used in the tensor decomposition.
